      "id": "mem-feedback_kayna_site-beforeafterslider--prevent-dra",
      "content": "When the slider is inside a `<Link>` wrapper, dragging triggers the link navigation on pointer release. Fix:\n- Add `e.preventDefault()` inside `handlePointerDown` before `setPointerCapture`\n- Add `draggable={false}` on the container div\n- Add `onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); e.preventDefault() }}` on the container div\n- Layer order: **after** image is the base layer (always visible); **before** image is clipped to `inset(0 ${100-pct}% 0 0)` so it reveals left\n\n**Why:** User reported that ",
      "summary": "BeforeAfterSlider: prevent drag-to-navigate with pointer capture + stopPropagation",
