      "id": "mem-feedback_kayna_site-webp-frame-conversion--use-cwe",
      "content": "Use `/opt/homebrew/bin/cwebp -q 85` to convert PNG frames to WebP. Never use ffmpeg's `-c:v libwebp` for RGBA images.\n\n**Why:** ffmpeg's default libwebp produces VP8 encoding which drops the alpha channel. The kayna-site frames are RGBA (transparent background) and rendered with `mix-blend-mode: screen` — opaque white pixels from VP8 encoding cause the entire page to appear white. `cwebp` produces VP8X (extended) with a proper ALPH chunk. Verified via `webpinfo` (look for `Alpha: 1`).\n\n**How to ",
